		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			When is everyone going to realize EQ does not have anything to do with economics but rather it is a matter of convenience? Market for fletched arrows? It never even existed pre-luclin.<br><br>Yeah, I've fletched loads of silver-tipped arrows that I planned to use with Trueshot. After a couple of times doing that, I realized it just wasn't worth the hassle. Especially now, who is going to bother with consumable arrows and crappy bow damage when there are melee weapons available that enable you to do comparable or slightly better damage? Bye bye Ranger bots.<br><br>Specialty arrows? I'll believe when I see them. By specialty arrows I do not mean just slapping bane damage on them. First find a way to make arrows proc spells. Then we can talk about removing or restricting EQ. Otherwise, I suggest you actually log in and fletch a single bag pack full of Mithril arrows by running back and forth between Felwithe and Kelethin. Then tell me whether EQ existsts for the reason of economics or convenience.<br><br>So afraid of archery that EQdesigners so strongly felt the need to create artificial lag in /autofire. When and if EQ becomes available to every melee classes, I bet that would be the first thing to go.<br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
