			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=30475'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=217992#M217992">157</a> of 206
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 786 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>When I said Endless Quiver keeps us from adding cool or fun upgrades, I'm not talking about making an arrow that has a higher base damage.&nbsp; That's just&nbsp;bumping baseline arrow damage, which would still happen&nbsp;even if we decided to make arrows that weren't affected by Endless Quiver.&nbsp;&nbsp;Endless Quiver exists mainly to take the tedium out of having to tote around&nbsp;hundreds of arrows to maintain a baseline bow&nbsp;damage.&nbsp; That's not going to change.&nbsp; All current arrows would still be affected by Endless Quiver and new arrows that exist to increase that baseline damage would still be affected by Endless Quiver as well.</P>
<P>But while Endless Quiver does a great job in its task of removing that tedium, at the same time its blanket effect prevents us from creating any "big bang" arrows that would be balanced if they were used up when shot.&nbsp; I'm talking about arrows that&nbsp;explode into fireballs when they hit a target, arrows that do massive damage (or even outright kill) creatures of a particular race, arrows that freeze a target and remove it from combat temporarily.&nbsp; Basically,&nbsp;I'd love for rangers to be able to reach back into their quiver and pull out something more than just a normal arrow but when every arrow in the game is never consumed, it makes doing that extremely difficult.</P>
<P>Rashere</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-17-2006</span> <span class=time_text>10:58 AM</span>
		</span>
