			>
			<div><span><br><blockquote><hr>gcubed wrote:<br><div></div><div><span><br><br>Three. Just what do you expect to charge for something like this in the bazaar? You stated in one of your posts a few gold per arrow to produce. If by a few you mean between 3 and 8 we can expect such an item to cost between 6 platinum and 16 platinum to make. Innitially you might be able to charge around 100 platinum (by price gouging) for each of these. Eventually (quite rapidly) as enough fletchers started selling these things the prices drop to be between 6.5 and 20 platinum. In order for you to keep enough of these things on hand to make any worthwhile amount of money from them they would have to be stackable which also means that they would be stackable in inventory or you would need to keep the prices up. One way to keep prices up is to limit supply. If you limit supply you will essentially reduce archery to a pulling tool or something used by the ramp tank. This will lower your proposed clients to what it is now (warriors and knights) thus lowering the demand and the prices drop again back down to about 6.5 and 20 platinum. You would also an even lower inventory turnover (they won't sell fast). Another way to keep prices up would give this proposed fletch item a very high trivial. Now suddenly this arrow summoner becomes a skill up path. The market will be flooded with them and you will be forced to sell the item at a loss.<br><br><br>In short selling arrows (or your arrow summoning device) will not make anyone rich even if SOE were to totally remove EQ from the game. At best it will keep you in healing potions. At worst you will take a loss every time you create them.<br><br><br></span></div><p>Message Edited by gcubed on <span class="date_text">04-17-2006</span><span class="time_text">01:42 PM</span></p><br><hr></blockquote><br>A little math for you. A few gold per arrow on a device that summons 20 stacks of 100 arrows = a lot more than 20 plat. The price woudl have to be set at a point where it would be worthwhile to the tradeskiller but not outrageous for the ranger, and where medium quality arrows would be cheap and plentiful and &quot;special&quot; arrows would be pricey enough that they would be worthwhile for special fights but not something you would use every day. I don't think that's impossible. There are multiple expendable items (potions, halas meat pies, etc) that I have been buying in the bazaar from tradeskillers on a regular basis for years. I would be happy to buy arrows in the same way but because anything decent is so expensive it is totally impractical WITHOUT endless quiver, I never buy arrows, I just summon crappy ones for pulling and accept that I'm gonna do 50 dps on range fights. Anyway, any numbers in my post are just pulled out of the air, I am just trying to communicate the concept.<br></span></div>	
