			>
			<span><br><blockquote><hr>gcubed wrote:<br><div><span><br><blockquote><hr>Rashere wrote:<br><div></div><p>When I said Endless Quiver keeps us from adding cool or fun upgrades, I'm not talking about making an arrow that has a higher base damage. That's justbumping baseline arrow damage, which would still happeneven if we decided to make arrows that weren't affected by Endless Quiver.Endless Quiver exists mainly to take the tedium out of having to tote aroundhundreds of arrows to maintain a baseline bowdamage. That's not going to change. All current arrows would still be affected by Endless Quiver and new arrows that exist to increase that baseline damage would still be affected by Endless Quiver as well.</p><p>But while Endless Quiver does a great job in its task of removing that tedium, at the same time its blanket effect prevents us from creating any &quot;big bang&quot; arrows that would be balanced if they were used up when shot. I'm talking about arrows thatexplode into fireballs when they hit a target, arrows that do massive damage (or even outright kill) creatures of a particular race, arrows that freeze a target and remove it from combat temporarily. Basically,I'd love for rangers to be able to reach back into their quiver and pull out something more than just a normal arrow but when every arrow in the game is never consumed, it makes doing that extremely difficult.</p><p>Rashere</p><br><hr></blockquote>Outright kill? As in a ranger (or anyone else with a bow) being able to headshot Overlord Mata Muram? Not only would something like that have to be consumable it would have to be very, very, very rare. Whether the rarity is by an insanely high fletching trivial or rare drops. Something like that could only be allowed in game at best once every 50 clearings of Anguish. Not only would something like that have to be rare it would have to be extremely temporary (i.e., cannot be taken out of zone, will not suvive a death, will go poof after a set amount of time.)<br><br>Arrows like that would be fun to play with, even if you missed one third of the time. An arrow with a 20k nuke, a ranger dropping a bomb like that would probably find it worth the inevitable summon/ranger parts all over zone that would ensue.<br><br><br>I like these concepts. Please tell me more. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br><br></span></div><br><hr></blockquote><br>I think you are taking Rashere's examples too literally. If you really want to analyze the killshot example, it would be easy enough to implement by using a charm-esque flag (or even the very same flag). If the mob can't be charmed then it shouldn't be KO'd in a shot either.<br><br>Anyways, things like crowd control arrows would be nice but with EQ the ranger would only need to acquire it once and would have the added utility forever possibly causing large balance issues. Personally, I'm not sure whether something like that is worth adding to the game at all if it is too powerful to be kept.<br><br></span><div></div>
