			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Jarsh92 wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Rashere wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>When I said Endless Quiver keeps us from adding cool or fun upgrades, I'm not talking about making an arrow that has a higher base damage.&nbsp; That's just&nbsp;bumping baseline arrow damage, which would still happen&nbsp;even if we decided to make arrows that weren't affected by Endless Quiver.&nbsp;&nbsp;Endless Quiver exists mainly to take the tedium out of having to tote around&nbsp;hundreds of arrows to maintain a baseline bow&nbsp;damage.&nbsp; That's not going to change.&nbsp; All current arrows would still be affected by Endless Quiver and new arrows that exist to increase that baseline damage would still be affected by Endless Quiver as well.</P>
<P>But while Endless Quiver does a great job in its task of removing that tedium, at the same time its blanket effect prevents us from creating any "big bang" arrows that would be balanced if they were used up when shot.&nbsp; I'm talking about arrows that&nbsp;explode into fireballs when they hit a target, arrows that do massive damage (or even outright kill) creatures of a particular race, <STRONG>arrows that freeze a target and remove it from combat temporarily.</STRONG>&nbsp; Basically,&nbsp;I'd love for rangers to be able to reach back into their quiver and pull out something more than just a normal arrow but when every arrow in the game is never consumed, it makes doing that extremely difficult.</P>
<P>Rashere</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I hope you are referring to a snare or root type arrow and not a mez.&nbsp; If you are referring to a mez, then I feel bad for all the enchanters as they will have yet another class competiting with their CC ability.</P>
<P>But I do agree it would be cool to have more arrow options and it just makes sense.&nbsp; Arrows that explode, etc would be awesome.<BR></P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Actually, last I checked the enchanters (or some of them at least) were encouraging more classes to get limited mez abilities, as it would allow more content to be designed to require or make mez a very useful tool.	
