		" 
			>
			<div></div><p>Some day I hope to move into Anguish and obtain my 2.0. I hope soon thata Darkglint will be mine soon. And as my melee dps increases, yes in order to do my part i'll be heading in to melee. The game now is set up that as you progress in the game a specific set of aa's enable to archery to come out of the depths of barely useable to down right fearsome. While pushing through the lower 60's I would get groups on my having AM3 and endless. Then as I neared 70 and aa's climbed through defensives and melee aa's my bow becomes less and less a factor. Especially now that I have 1.5 and Eclipse my melee is obviously better.</p><p>From the point I am in the game the minor increase of trick shot (6% I hear) is all I have to look forward to. I Plaque is some time off. The clockwork I have now is pretty much top bow I can obtain atm. (Don't start. I like it)</p><p>Some great Ideas have been mentioned in this thread. Leave endless alone but put in some Raid drop arrows that have a countdown in use. 16dmg but after 100 shots poof. Make a quiver that would acctually sit in the ammo slot like it's supposed to. I like the repairing your bow thing. My master fletching would acctually get used and it would reguvinize the skill. Revamp Endless to be 3 aa's for 50% use,6 for 75% and 9 for 95%. I can live without endless if replaced with almost endless. This would allow others to get lvl 1 of the aa line but keep rangers ahead of the rest. 95% wouldn't be to bad. 1000 arrows of a raid, I would only loose 50. That's have a stack. Now hopefully the parts to make higher end bows would be made a bit more common to drop would make crafting 50 drakespikes not cost 20k. Bring that number down to 1kish and it's a bit more reasonable. Trick or effects arrows, imo would be more of a gimik than a use. Flame arrows and Frost arrows only have a limit'd use now. Hey how about a slot 4aug for my bow that isn't just stats or spell guard 3. How about a bane dmg aug or bow haste or clickie dmg effect?</p><p>I still feel if sony intended use to be a mainly melee class there wouldn't be a bow in my inventory screen. I just want them to be closer in dps. I personally can get alot more done for the raid by shooting. If my raid leader wants me in melee, in I go. When not raiding I'm a power soloer. My bow is my primary means of weak'ning mobs before I dive in to finish em off. I'm a proud ranger.</p><p>I'm not trying to knock those rangers that pref melee but well all don't pref that.</p>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							A Rangers life is truly to oversee these worlds with a mighty bow and deadly aim. <br><br>Proud owner of Ikk Gear and Winner of Uqua!!!!<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1214435">70 Hunter Naultarous<br>Silverbow</a>
